---
const problems = [
  {
    title: 'AI ships bugs at scale',
    description:
      "Your agents generate 500 lines in 10 minutes. But Agent 2's auth refactor broke Agent 1's API contract. Nobody caught it until production. The faster AI codes, the faster bugs compound.",
    contrast: 'Tmonier validates cross-agent changes before anything merges.',
  },
  {
    title: 'You became the integration layer',
    description:
      "5 agents, 5 worktrees, 5 diffs to review. You're the only one who sees the full picture — and you're doing it manually, across tabs, with no tooling. AI was supposed to save you time. Instead, you're a full-time code reviewer for robots.",
    contrast: 'Tmonier gives you one dashboard, structured checkpoints, and conflict detection.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Nobody owns the architecture anymore',
    description:
      'Each agent optimizes locally. None of them know your service boundaries, your naming conventions, or what was decided last sprint. The codebase drifts — not in one session, but across dozens. Death by a thousand AI commits.',
    contrast: 'Tmonier enforces architectural memory across every agent, every session.',
  },
];
---

<section class="problem-section" style="background: #F5F0E8; padding: 5rem 2.5rem;">
  <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">

    <div style="margin-bottom: 3.5rem; max-width: 680px;">
      <p
        style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 4px; color: rgba(11,26,46,0.35); text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0 0 1.2rem;"
      >
        The problem
      </p>
      <h2
        style="font-family: 'Vollkorn', serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.2vw, 2.5rem); color: #0B1A2E; margin: 0 0 1rem; line-height: 1.2;"
      >
        Your AI agents are fast.<br />But fast without guardrails is dangerous.
      </h2>
      <p
        style="font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-size: 1.05rem; color: #4A5568; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;"
      >
        Parallel AI agents multiply your output. They also multiply your risk. Without orchestration, speed becomes your most expensive liability.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div
      style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem;"
      class="problem-grid"
    >
      {
        problems.map((p) => (
          <div
            style="background: #fff; border: 1px solid #E8E0D0; border-radius: 8px; padding: 2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: space-between;"
          >
            <div>
              <h3
                style="font-family: 'Vollkorn', serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.15rem; color: #0B1A2E; margin: 0 0 0.9rem; line-height: 1.3;"
              >
                {p.title}
              </h3>
              <p
                style="font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #4A5568; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 1.75rem;"
              >
                {p.description}
              </p>
            </div>
            <p
              style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: #0B1A2E; border-top: 1px solid #E8E0D0; padding-top: 1.1rem; margin: 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;"
            >
              <span style="color: #C49A2B;">&rarr;</span>
              {p.contrast}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem-section {
    min-height: 100vh;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .problem-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
    }
  }
</style>
